history.content: Data 100 is a pretty light workload class that teaches you the basics of common data science tools that are used in industry. I really enjoyed the class and feel like I learned a decent amount of applicable content when I took it.

I'm a senior going in to my last semester at Cal. Next semester I will be working part time (15-25 hours per week) as a back end engineer. I don't have any CS requirements left other than EE16A, so I'm just looking for an interesting class that preferably has a lot of industry application and not a crazy high workload. So far I have taken:

  • 161, 162, 168, 170, 186, 188

164 seems really interesting and like it would help with my programming ability, but I think that the workload might be too high since it is being taught by Hilfinger. 189 also seems interesting, but I haven't taken 53 so I'm afraid I'd be lost. Are those fears reasonable, or should I take one of those? Are there any other grad classes that are manageable for undergrads?
history.subject: Course suggestions?
